			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>bugfinder wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Does seem weird that in mob vs pet senarios bst pets seem to last longer than ours... But thats the seond time Ive read that in a direct bst vs mage we won...  Did the bst put their best proc on their pet?? 
<br />

<br />
The only other thing to ask is what AAs each of you had.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
its not weird. the beast pet is tanking a slowed mob and the mage pet isnt. 
<br />
look at xalmats parse. you dont see beast pet vs unslowed mob. because beasts dont let mobs not be slowed. 
<br />

<br />
according to some things i saw around the time of the pet fixes rytan did rathes son has about 7% more mitigation over a beast warder. then when you add in the armor that comes preequipped on the mage pet it goes to about 20%. however that still isnt a 65% slow. and it would show up in the parses as nearly a 45% shift in damage taken per second over a lenght of time. hmmm thats about what xalmats wonderfull comparison showed. 
<br />

<br />
if you would like to parse a dpoc focus'd rathes son or ward of xegony against a slowed crystaline golem i'll be more than happy to help you out. you'll see the pet tanks better than the warder parses that were offerered up as proof by xalmat.  
<br />

<br />
you can find me on the saryrn server. weekends are always best for me for extended testing of stuff. you'll need to bring your own cleric. but i can supply both the mage and the beast for the test. 
<br />

<br />
as far as pet vs pet goes. 
<br />
if i slow rathes son or ms4 my warder kicks the crap outta it. 
<br />
much like if you ds rathes son or ms4 my warder beats itself to death on it. but that isnt a true pet vs pet comparison. and neither was the parses xalmat used in his pet healing comparison. a 65% slowed crystaline golem is NOT the same mob as a full speed crystaline golem. 
<br />

<br />
this is what ive been trying to explain but noone seems to want to listen. everyone is so caught up with beast pets tank better they neglect to look at why. 
<br />

<br />
for adding survivability to your pet snare > slow > healing. this is why necro pets last so damn long. if they dont have to tank they live forever. 
<br />
it doesnt matter that both mage pets and beast pets kick the snot out of them in duels. the pet is a 1 time cast 70dps dot that they can basically forget about other than /pet taunt off /pet attack. 
<br />

<br />
to be perfectly honest i happen to think my lvl 60 warder would outtank rathes son if the warder was  against a 65% slowed mob and rathes son was against an unslowed mob. max hit againt the pet would be higher but less atacks means less damage taken.
<br />

<br />
i hope im making myself clear. im not against mage upgrades. heck if they fix the class i might actuall be tempted to unretire my mage. but i will argue all day against incorrect evidence used to support the bolstering of the class or call for nerfs of another class. 
<br />

<br />
let me further clarify i am for increaseing the mage heal's hp/sec. but asking for spirit of sorsha is not what you want. trust me. if you need to heal your pet it is far to slow to be an effective means. sure if you want the pet to tank poi mobs while you heal it its great. but beyond that it is too slow of a cast to reliably keep the pet alive against an unslowed mob. 
<br />

<br />
this is why i proposed a bulwark of vie type spell. 10% direct mitigation buff up. decreasing the cast time of planar renewal to 6 seconds and dropping the recast timer to 2.25 seconds would make it a far more effective spell. by allowing mages to dump mana into the pet to keep it alive in an offtanking situation for someone to slow the mob or the group to finish up the other target but still not efficient enough as a means of solo. you see i think sony would buy that logic. Rytan specifically said anything geared at soloing would be a hard sell.
<br />

<br />
and if soloing is really what you want to do then you need to do it like the professional soloers. with snare. because 100% damage avoidance is better than any amount of mitigation you can have without just plain making the pet immune to melee.<br />_________________<br />tezron
<br />

<br />
This message has been brought to you by the letter Z and the number 42</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
